===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{sense|concrete}}
## a [[trail]] for the use of, or worn by, [[pedestrian]]s.
## a [[course]] taken.
## {{context|paganism}} A [[pagan|Pagan]] tradition, for example [[witchcraft]], [[Wicca]], [[druidism]], [[Heathenry]].
# {{context|abstract}}
## a [[metaphorical]] course.
## a [[method]] or [[direction]] of proceeding.
## {{graph theory}} a [[sequence]] of [[vertex|vertices]] from one vertex to another using the arcs ([[edge|edges]]). A path does not visit the same vertex more than once (unless it is a ''closed path'', where only the first and the last vertex are the same).
## {{topology}} a [[continuous map]] <math>f</math>  from the [[unit interval]] <math>I = [0,1]</math> to a [[topological space]] <math>X</math>.

